  "prompt": "What's the biggest failure of Google?",
  "response": "One of Google's most significant failures is considered to be Google+, its attempt to compete with Facebook in social networking. Launched in 2011, Google+ failed to gain substantial user traction and was ultimately shut down for consumers in April 2019. Despite significant initial investment and mandatory integration with other Google services, it never achieved the critical mass of users or engagement that the company hoped for. Other notable Google failures include Google Wave, Google Glass (for consumer market), and Google Buzz, but Google+ is often cited as one of their most prominent unsuccessful projects.",
